electTurn.memo:
Override Permission

In principle, a student should not be permitted to take a course without satisfying the prerequisites. This is mainly to protect the student from being struggling or even failed in the class without adequate preparation. However, instructor(s) may give overriding permission to a student by evaluating the student’s knowledge background.

Apply at http://bpm.umji.sjtu.edu.cn/  to waive the prerequisites, and ask the course instructor to approve it online. An interview may be required by the instructor.

  

Workload

The maximum number of credits a full-time student can take in a regular semester is 18, on top of the MOE and SJTU requirements, and the minimum is 12 (0 for spring). There is one exception that students at the last term of study are not restricted by the minimum credit requirement.

Apply at http://bpm.umji.sjtu.edu.cn/ to exceed the limit. Freshmen in their first term are not allowed to apply for overload!

The undergraduate committee will review the applications.

 

Time Conflict

Students are not allowed to take courses under time conflict. Senior students may consult the undergraduate office if it is absolutely necessary for graduation.

 

Enrollment and Cap

Each course requires a minimum registration number. Courses with very small enrollment number will be cancelled.

The course instructor can decide the class cap. However, to ensure students have equal chances, basically the course instructor is NOT allowed to appoint specific students to enroll his/her class or override the cap according to his/her personal preference. Students are not allowed to approach the instructor or staff for personal benefit too!

 

Retaking Courses

Student may retake a course when the grade is below C. All grades will be shown on the transcripts, but only the last grade will be counted in GPA and to satisfy the graduation requirements.

 

Tuition

Courses may charge extra tuition on credit basis in the spring semester, or in a regular semester for non full-time students. 

Tuition per credit = Annual tuition/32 

 

Prohibitions

Students on suspension or exchange programs should not register any courses.

 

Penalty

If you break any of the academic rules, your enrollment status can be cancelled eventually!
